For juristi- cal writers sometimes by an abusc of language call that, natural obli- yation, which it is by nature a handsome thing to do, though it is not truly due: as for an executor to pay legacies entire without the deductiori which the Falcidian law allows; to pay a just debt when the creditor has been deprived of his legal right by a pcnal sentence 3 to return a benefit for a benefit3 none of which can be recovered by an action of false debt.
